    • Method Detail

      • generateLicenseNumber

        public static LicenseNumber generateLicenseNumber​(Name driverName,
                                                  java.util.Date licenseDateOfIssue)
                                           throws java.lang.Exception
        Static factory method to generate a unique license number for the driver details passed into it. The license number consists of three sections separated by dashes. The first portion consists of the driver's initials, the second section is the year of issue of the license, finally a two digit number to ensure multiple drivers with the same initials and date of issue have a unique license. A driver whose first initial is D and last initial is K with a date of issue of 2005 would have a license which looks like "DK-2005-45". A map is used to ensure uniqueness, if the license already exists, the number to be used for the final section will be iterated and the license will try and be created again.
        Parameters:
        driverName - the name of the driver
        licenseDateOfIssue - date of issue of the driver's license
        Returns:
        newly generated LicenseNumber
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - should there be 100 drivers with the same initials and date of issue and no more unique licenses be available for that driver
